   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Domain Chatbot\\n\",\"**NLP Project 51 of 100** — Build a topic-specific chatbot using document retrieval + LLM.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in ['numpy','sentence-transformers','scikit-learn']:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace('-','_'))\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, requests\\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\\nfrom sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nmodel = SentenceTransformer('all-MiniLM-L6-v2')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Knowledge base (Python programming domain)\\nKB = [\\n    'Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language created by Guido van Rossum in 1991.',\\n    'Lists in Python are mutable ordered sequences. Use append() to add items and pop() to remove.',\\n    'Dictionaries store key-value pairs. Access values with dict[key] or dict.get(key, default).',\\n    'Functions are defined with the def keyword. Use *args for variable positional arguments.',\\n    'Classes define objects with attributes and methods. Use __init__ for initialization.',\\n    'Virtual environments isolate project dependencies. Use python -m venv to create one.',\\n    'pip is the package manager for Python. Use pip install package_name to install packages.',\\n    'List comprehensions provide concise syntax: [x**2 for x in range(10)].',\\n    'Exception handling uses try/except blocks. Always catch specific exceptions.',\\n    'Type hints improve code readability: def greet(name: str) -> str.',\\n]\\n\\nkb_embeddings = model.encode(KB)\\nprint(f'Knowledge base: {len(KB)} entries')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"def chat(question, top_k=2):\\n    q_emb = model.encode([question])\\n    sims = cosine_similarity(q_emb, kb_embeddings)[0]\\n    top_idx = sims.argsort()[-top_k:][::-1]\\n    context = '\\\\n'.join(KB[i] for i in top_idx)\\n    \\n    # Try LLM answer\\n    prompt = f'Answer the question using only the context below. Be concise.\\\\n\\\\nContext:\\\\n{context}\\\\n\\\\nQuestion: {question} /no_think'\\n    try:\\n        r = requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/generate',json={'model':'qwen3:1.7b','prompt':prompt,'stream':False},timeout=60)\\n        return r.json().get('response', context)\\n    except:\\n        return f'Based on our knowledge base:\\\\n{context}'\\n\\nquestions = ['How do I create a list in Python?','What are virtual environments?','How do I handle errors?']\\nfor q in questions:\\n    print(f'Q: {q}')\\n    print(f'A: {chat(q)}')\\n    print()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Domain chatbots combine retrieval + generation** for grounded answers.\\n\",\"- **Sentence embeddings enable semantic matching** beyond keyword overlap.\\n\",\"- **LLM synthesizes retrieved context** into natural answers.\\n\",\"- **For production, add conversation history** and feedback loops.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
